<h1>About Morse Code Encoder & Decoder</h1>

<p>
  This app allows you to convert text into Morse code and decode Morse code back into text.
</p>

<h2>Encoding</h2>
<p>
  The <strong>encode</strong> function takes a string, converts it to uppercase, and replaces each character with its Morse code equivalent from a predefined dictionary. Spaces are added between Morse characters for readability.
</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<pre>
Input: "HELLO"
Output: ".... . .-.. .-.. ---"
</pre>

<h2>Decoding</h2>
<p>
  The <strong>decode</strong> function takes a string of Morse code, splits it by spaces, and converts each Morse symbol back into the corresponding letter using a reverse dictionary. This ensures efficient and accurate translation back to text.
</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<pre>
Input: ".... . .-.. .-.. ---"
Output: "HELLO"
</pre>

<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>We use a <code>Morse</code> class with <code>encode</code> and <code>decode</code> methods.</li>
  <li>Encoding and decoding operations are O(n) in the length of the input.</li>
  <li>We create a reverse dictionary for decoding so that lookup is fast (O(1)) for each character.</li>
</ul>
